{
  "texts": [
    "These nets were initially designed for collecting plankton and can sieve large volumes of flowing water 38.",
    "The 3D porous structure of the AgF@AgM@C10 is intended to be like a Neuston net capable of trapping MPs from flowing solutions using a combination of capillary and hydrophobic forces.",
    "MPs adsorb and accumulate on the surfaces of AgF@AgM@C10 due to hydrophobic and capillary forces.",
    "We initially flowed suspensions of PS (1.06 × 10 4 particles per liter or MPs L -1) and PE (1.9 × 10 4 MPs L-1) through the AgF@AgM@C10 substrate (Suppl. Fig.",
    "22) for 20 min."
  ]
}